transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Customer Service, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'd like to order an AGV.

Speaker 1: Sure, have you ordered one of those before?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me go out of this.

Speaker 2: What's your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: My name is Antonio Petrone. It's March 16, 1955.

Speaker 2: Are you still on Westport Drive?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, and you want to get 100 milligrams, how many tablets?

Speaker 1: Ten.

Speaker 2: All right, and you want to use the card on file or do you want to update the card?

Speaker 1: Which one do you have on file?

Speaker 2: It says $37.92.

Speaker 1: Yes, how much will it be?

Speaker 2: It'll be $49.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Is that a one-time orâ€”

Speaker 1: Oops.

Speaker 2: Give me a second, sorry.

Speaker 1: One second.

Speaker 2: It's up to you.

Speaker 1: You can do one time, you can have every couple of months,

Speaker 2: or we can just pause it so you can see how you like it.

Speaker 1: Because when you have the membership on, you're able to get discounts.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I can call you if I want to cancel, is that what you're saying?

Speaker 1: Yes, so if we leave it on, it'll allow you to get discounts.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, let's do that.

Speaker 2: Okay, I've processed that for you, and then I'm just going to pause it for a few months

Speaker 1: so that you have time to try it out.

Speaker 2: And then you can call back if you need anything sooner

Speaker 1: or if you want to pause it again or anything like that, okay?

Speaker 2: All right, and that's the NGV you got?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: It was before it wasn't NGV, right?

Speaker 1: Nope, it was not.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Because it didn't work at all.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, you have a good day.

Speaker 1: You too, thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
